item.title: Python and R
item.description: Square bracks ([]) define a list. Indexing begins at 0, so the first element is at the 0th position. The nth element will be located in the (n-1)th position. personal_dict = {'firstName':'Cathy', 'lastName':"Nguyen", 'hobbies':['tennis','ice skating', 'singing', 'paper crafting'],'occupation':'student','age':22} print(personal_dict) ## {'firstName': 'Cathy', 'lastName': 'Nguyen', 'hobbies': ['tennis', 'ice skating', 'singing', 'paper crafting'], 'occupation': 'student', 'age': 22} Cinnamon Roll Hug
